# EmpiRE-Compass Design System

## Welcome to EmpiRE-Compass
*"Navigating the EmpiRE of Empirical Research in Requirements Engineering"*

---

## 🔬 About the Project

EmpiRE-Compass is a comprehensive platform that facilitates the exploration, reproduction, and enrichment of empirical research data within the KG-EmpiRE ecosystem. By leveraging live data from the Open Research Knowledge Graph (ORKG), EmpiRE-Compass offers researchers a suite of tools for data visualization, comparative analysis, and structured data contribution—all while aligning with ACM standards.

## 🎯 Key Features

### 📊 Interactive Dashboards
- Live data visualization from ORKG
- 16 competency questions with dynamic answers
- Real-time statistics and metrics

### 🔄 Research Reproduction
- Historical state comparison
- Data evolution tracking
- Reproducibility tools

### 📈 Statistics & Analytics
- Conference and paper metrics
- RDF triple analysis
- Resource and literal counting

### 🤝 Collaboration Tools
- Survey-based data contribution
- Curator approval workflow
- ACM standards alignment

### 🧭 Study Designer
- Similar research identification
- Design recommendations
- Knowledge base integration

## 🎨 Design System Overview

This Storybook contains the complete component library for EmpiRE-Compass, organized into the following categories:

### 📱 Layout Components
- Header, Footer, Navigation
- Responsive containers and grids
- Menu and drawer systems

### 🏠 Home Page Components
- Hero sections and feature highlights
- Contact forms and partner displays
- Project information sections

### 📊 Data Visualization
- Custom charts and graphs
- Statistics cards and displays
- Interactive data components

### 🔧 Utility Components
- Loading and error states
- Form elements and inputs
- Modal and dialog systems

### 🤖 AI Components
- AI Assistant interface
- Chat message components
- Dynamic question handlers

## 🛠️ Technology Stack

- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript, Material-UI
- **State Management**: Redux Toolkit
- **Routing**: React Router v7
- **Charts**: Material-UI X-Charts
- **Styling**: Material-UI Theme System
- **Backend**: Firebase Firestore
- **Build**: Vite
- **Testing**: Storybook, Vitest

